# agentpipe — example shell env vars for Claude Code.
#
# This file is NOT auto-installed and NOT auto-sourced. It's a curated reference.
# To use any of these, copy what you want into your shell rc (~/.zshrc / ~/.bashrc),
# or copy this whole file to ~/.claude/agentpipe.env and add this line to your rc:
#
#     [ -f ~/.claude/agentpipe.env ] && source ~/.claude/agentpipe.env
#
# All variables are documented at:
#     https://code.claude.com/docs/en/env-vars
#     https://code.claude.com/docs/en/data-usage
#
# Why this isn't auto-installed: shell-rc is the user's territory. Sourcing
# unfamiliar env vars by default is invasive and stack-specific (some users
# want telemetry on, some want max effort, some don't). Pick what fits.

# --------------------------------------------------------------------
# Reasoning effort
# --------------------------------------------------------------------
# Sets the per-turn reasoning budget. Valid: low | medium | high | xhigh | max | auto.
# Default since Feb-Mar 2026 is "medium" with adaptive thinking, which can sometimes
# allocate 0 reasoning tokens — leading to fabricated SHAs / packages / APIs.
# (Boris Cherny / Anthropic confirmed this on HN: news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47664442)
#
# "max" removes the per-turn cap. On Sonnet 4.6 / Opus 4.6 this materially improves
# heavy engineering work, BUT can blow through paid-plan quotas faster.
# "high" is a safer default if you're on a metered plan.
# Override per-task with the /effort slash command.
#
# export CLAUDE_CODE_EFFORT_LEVEL=max

# --------------------------------------------------------------------
# Adaptive thinking
# --------------------------------------------------------------------
# Disables the adaptive-reasoning behavior that can emit zero reasoning tokens.
# IMPORTANT: This var is a NO-OP on Opus 4.7 — that model is always adaptive
# at the API level. It only takes effect on Opus 4.6 / Sonnet 4.6 (CC >= 2.1.111).
#
# export CLAUDE_CODE_DISABLE_ADAPTIVE_THINKING=1

# --------------------------------------------------------------------
# Auto-compact threshold
# --------------------------------------------------------------------
# By default Claude Code compacts the conversation when the context window is
# ~95% full — by then coherence has already degraded. Lowering the threshold
# triggers compaction earlier (cleaner state, but more frequent compactions).
# Validate the var name in current docs before relying on it; the canonical
# alternative is the in-session /compact command and /clear between tasks.
#
# export CLAUDE_AUTOCOMPACT_PCT_OVERRIDE=70

# --------------------------------------------------------------------
# Privacy: disable non-essential traffic
# --------------------------------------------------------------------
# Bundle that sets all of these at once:
#     CLAUDE_CODE_DISABLE_AUTOUPDATER
#     CLAUDE_CODE_DISABLE_TELEMETRY
#     CLAUDE_CODE_DISABLE_ERROR_REPORTING
#     CLAUDE_CODE_DISABLE_FEEDBACK_COMMAND
# Trade-off: anonymous telemetry helps Anthropic surface bugs faster. Off by
# choice, not by default.
#
# export CLAUDE_CODE_DISABLE_NONESSENTIAL_TRAFFIC=1
